		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hmm, I was thinking about Squeedo, but I don't know why I didn't think of it as a custom mapper. If I were to make a custom mapper, it'd be like MMC1, but with like 1024k of PRG allowed, or something like that. I was just thinking about it, because I am going to be developing FF7 NES sometime in the future, and I was just thinking "What if I ran out of space"? I'm using 512k PRG with MMC1, and I really wish I was allowed 1024k. If I could make my own mapper, that'd be just great. But I don't know C/C++ to make my own emu, and I wouldn't want to have to pester someone to update an emu just for my own mapper. Thanks though, I've been wondering that for a long time <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />.
<br />
<br />EDIT: I was about to put this in the hardware section, then I thought it had to do more with the developement of the NES.

		

