	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Building your own mapper with mmc1 like capabilities would not be easy.  However expanding mmc1 to 1024KB would be pretty easy.  You would just need to do the same trick as Dragon Warrior 3/4 used, and steal the upper 2 chr address lines (chr a15 and a16) and wire them to the prg instead (prg a18 and a19).  This gives you 1MB prg and 32KB chr.  Emulators already have to do the dw 3/4 change so I dont think they would have problems doing it for your game.  Emulators with good plugin modules should be simple to update.  Your code just has to be careful when swapping chr banks to leave the prg bits the same.
<br />
<br />This is just a wiring change on the board.  There is NO special mmc1 version that supports more memory.  You can use the chip from any mmc1 board.  
<br />
<br />(edit: WRONG) A bigger problem would be actually making the board.  A 1MB eprom/flash chip would not fit in any board and you would likely need to use 2x 512KB anyways.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


