	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />From a hardware/software design point for your game, using the octal ff looks much better than mmc1.  Both designs would need to be added to emulators and both are simple.  However if you want to produce a small number of carts looks like there is a good mmc1 board you can use.  Search the <a href="http://www.parodius.com/~veilleux/boardtable.txt" class="postlink">board table</a> for SNROM or SJROM which has 256k prg, 8k vram, and 8k wram + battery.   Then get a <a href="http://www.tranzistoare.ro/datasheets/185/180793_DS.pdf" class="postlink">27C080</a> or similar and use the datasheet pinout to compare to <a href="http://nesdev.com/NES%20ROM%20Pinouts.txt" class="postlink">256KB prg pinout</a> for the rewiring.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


