	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />SJROM has actually CHRROM, and only 28-pin CHR chips can fit in it, wich differs it from SKROM, wich has both 32-pin slots, and from SAROM, wich has both 28-pin slots.
<br />For some reason, rumors float arround that SJROM has CHRRAM, but this is wrong, SJROM is like SKROM but it support only small CHR sizes.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


